# Gogols.ai Cursor Rules

## Project Context
This is the Gogols.ai website - a specialized AI agents platform with a cyberpunk aesthetic. The brand positions AI agents as "digital souls" that can be trained, experienced, and deployed.

## Brand Identity
- **Colors:** Use Gogols brand tokens (bg-gogol-bg, text-gogol-cyan, bg-gogol-surface, etc.) - NEVER hardcode hex colors
- **Theme:** Dark theme by default (className="dark" on html)
- **Aesthetic:** Cyber-noir, holographic gradients, neon accents
- **Voice:** Intelligent, mythic, slightly uncanny, cyber-romantic

## Code Standards
- TypeScript for all files
- Next.js App Router conventions
- Use shadcn/ui components when possible
- Follow existing patterns in src/app/page.tsx
- Use semantic color tokens: text-foreground, text-muted-foreground, border-border

## Styling Rules
- ALWAYS use brand tokens: bg-gogol-bg, text-gogol-cyan, bg-gogol-surface, etc.
- NEVER hardcode colors like bg-[#0b0c10] or text-cyan-300
- Use Tailwind utility classes
- Prefer shadcn/ui components over custom implementations

## File Structure
- Components: src/components/
- UI components: src/components/ui/ (shadcn)
- Pages: src/app/
- Utilities: src/lib/
- Public assets: public/

## Component Patterns
- Buttons: Use shadcn Button, h-11 px-6 for main CTAs
- Cards: bg-gogol-surface/40 or bg-card, border-border, rounded-xl
- Sections: px-6 py-16 md:py-24, border-t border-border, max-w-5xl/6xl mx-auto

## When Adding Features
1. Check shadcn/ui for existing components
2. Use brand tokens, not hardcoded values
3. Maintain dark theme compatibility
4. Test responsive design
5. Follow existing patterns

